### Wish Management API Demo
# Variables
@host = http://localhost:8080/api

### 1. Welcome Endpoint
# Verify the API is running.
GET {{host}}/welcome

### 2. Create a New Wish
# Add a new wish to the list.
POST {{host}}/wishes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "New Laptop",
  "comment": "MacBook Pro M3 Max",
  "link": "https://www.apple.com/macbook-pro/",
  "cameTrue": false
}

> {%
    client.global.set("wish_id", response.body.id);
%}

### 3. Get All Wishes (Paginated & Sorted)
# Retrieve a list of wishes. Supports page, size, sortBy, and direction parameters.

# Default call (page 0, size 10, sortBy updatedAt, direction DESC)
GET {{host}}/wishes?page=0&size=10&sortBy=updatedAt&direction=DESC

### 4. Get Wishes (Sorting by Name, Ascending)
GET {{host}}/wishes?page=0&size=5&sortBy=name&direction=ASC

### 5. Get Wishes (Second Page, Smaller Size)
GET {{host}}/wishes?page=1&size=2&sortBy=createdAt&direction=DESC

### 6. Get a Single Wish by ID
# Use the ID from the previous 'Create' request.
GET {{host}}/wishes/{{wish_id}}

### 7. Update an Existing Wish
# Update the wish created in step 2.
PUT {{host}}/wishes/{{wish_id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "New Laptop",
  "comment": "MacBook Pro M3 Max (Space Black)",
  "link": "https://www.apple.com/macbook-pro/",
  "cameTrue": false
}

### 8. Mark a Wish as Came True
# Specialized PATCH endpoint to update the status.
PATCH {{host}}/wishes/{{wish_id}}/came-true

### 9. Delete a Wish
# Soft-deletes the wish by ID.
DELETE {{host}}/wishes/{{wish_id}}

### 10. Health Check
# Check the application health via Spring Boot Actuator.
GET http://localhost:8080/actuator/health
